Put the flour and sugar in the jar and stir. Lightly beat in the milk, honey and oil until the mixture is a little doughy. Gently stir in the blueberries, being careful not to squash them.Microwave for 1 minute in an 800W microwave. Leave to stand for 2 minutes.Remove from the microwave with a tea towel (Caution: the jar may be still be hot). To serve, drizzle with honey and sprinkle over the blueberries.